candidates.title: Bug 1677448 - Implement the datetime metric in the RLB
candidates.body:
This implements the datetime metric in the rust language bindings.

Nothing special, except for the addition of the `test_get_value` function: unfortunately, we need to do the truncation ourselves, which is a big quirky (and also the reason why we're not doing that for the other bindings!).
